value.stringValue:
/* The bypass logic for jobs is special, due to rollups required to rollup job to date payments and receivable balance on the account and/or mass updates made via integration or user The first condition is as follows If bypass is not turned off for the current running user AND EITHER 1. It is a new record that has either the receivable balance or job to date payments filled out 2. OR it is a change to the receivable balance 3. OR it is a change to the payments received to date 4. OR it is a change to the account THEN we bypass the process builder and do nothing Finally, if we do have process builder turned off for the current user via DataAmin__c.TurnOffProcessBuilder__c IS TRUE, then we bypass the process builder and do nothing OR if the Job's Bypass Automation is TRUE ELSE, the process builder executes normally to the next step */ ( NOT($Setup.DataAdmin__c.TurnOffProcessBuilder__c ) && ( (ISNEW() && ([WorkOrder].Receivable_Balance__c <> 0 || [WorkOrder].Paid_to_Date__c <> 0)) || PRIORVALUE([WorkOrder].Receivable_Balance__c) <> [WorkOrder].Receivable_Balance__c || PRIORVALUE([WorkOrder].Paid_to_Date__c) <> [WorkOrder].Paid_to_Date__c ) )
|| $Setup.DataAdmin__c.TurnOffProcessBuilder__c || [WorkOrder].Bypass_Automation__c = TRUE

formulas.name: formula_myRule_1
formulas.expression:
/* The bypass logic for jobs is special, due to rollups required to rollup job to date payments and receivable balance on the account and/or mass updates made via integration or user The first condition is as follows If bypass is not turned off for the current running user AND EITHER 1. It is a new record that has either the receivable balance or job to date payments filled out 2. OR it is a change to the receivable balance 3. OR it is a change to the payments received to date 4. OR it is a change to the account THEN we bypass the process builder and do nothing Finally, if we do have process builder turned off for the current user via DataAmin__c.TurnOffProcessBuilder__c IS TRUE, then we bypass the process builder and do nothing OR if the Job's Bypass Automation is TRUE ELSE, the process builder executes normally to the next step */ ( NOT({!$Setup.DataAdmin__c.TurnOffProcessBuilder__c} ) && ( (ISNEW() && ({!myVariable_current.Receivable_Balance__c} <> 0 || {!myVariable_current.Paid_to_Date__c} <> 0)) || PRIORVALUE({!myVariable_current.Receivable_Balance__c}) <> {!myVariable_current.Receivable_Balance__c} || PRIORVALUE({!myVariable_current.Paid_to_Date__c}) <> {!myVariable_current.Paid_to_Date__c} ) )
|| {!$Setup.DataAdmin__c.TurnOffProcessBuilder__c} || {!myVariable_current.Bypass_Automation__c} = TRUE
